post_text:
Inclement Weather Announcement | August 27 Update

Due to safety concerns related to the forecasted track of Hurricane Laura, the following campuses in the Southeast portion of Texas will be closed and remote learning will be temporarily suspended.

Please continue to check our Facebook page for updated information. In the meantime, our thoughts are with those who find themselves in Laura's path and we look forward to safely restarting the school year once the storm has passed.

Premier High School - Dayton: Wednesday, Aug. 26 - Friday, Aug. 28

Premier High School - Houston North: Wednesday, Aug. 26 - Thursday, Aug. 27

Premier High School - Gallery Furniture North: Wednesday, Aug. 26 - Friday, Aug. 28

Premier High School - Huntsville: Thursday, Aug. 27

Premier High School - Little Rock & Premier High School - North Little Rock: Early Release Thursday, Aug. 27 at 2 p.m.

post_text:
We have received a number of questions about whether or not we intend to provide a remote learning option for the 2020-21 school year. The short answer is yes. On Tuesday, the TEA asked that all public schools in Texas offer remote instruction to families who request it.

We will share additional details about our remote and on-campus options, along with details about the 2020-21 school year in the near future. We appreciate your patience and look forward to working with you next year.

COVID-19 Texas Parent/Student Update | In response to Governor Abbott’s recent executive order, ResponsiveEd schools will remain closed and remote learning will continue for the remainder of the school year in accordance with TEA guidelines: https://bit.ly/2XJxx77. The announcement was made as part of the governor’s multi-phased plan to responsibly reopen the Texas economy.

During the press conference, Abbott said Texas Education Agency (TEA) Commissioner Mike Morath would share more details for schools in the near future. Once information becomes available we will notify you through our usual communication channels.

Thank you again for your partnership.

shared_text:
Premier High School - Austin North is with Trio Electric.
March 4 at 8:28 PM ·

Our TRIO students had a fantastic time visiting the Kalahari job site in Round Rock today! Mr. Sanchez, Mr. Rivera, Ms. Aleman and one of the TRIO Field Leaders took the time out of their schedule to show our students around the Kalahari Resort. These types of field trips allow our students to learn in a non-standard classroom setting. Thanks to our TRIO Pre-Apprenticeship Program, our students were able to get a preview of their possible future job! Thank you TRIO for allowing our students to visit the site! One of our students commented " I felt like I belonged, like I was meant to be there". This is Awesome!!
#TRIO #electrician #premierhighschool

post_text: Exciting news at Premier High School - Little Rock ! Tomorrow, the campus hosts its first "Teen Talk." The series will provide resources and support for the challenges and misconceptions scholars may face so they can be informed and encouraged in their future choices. #ProvidingHope
shared_text:
Premier High School - Little Rock
February 25 at 2:44 PM ·

Premier Little Rock
PHSLR Teen Talk: This Friday, Feb. 28 we will host the first in a series called Teen Talk. Teen Talk focuses on providing information and resources to our students regarding the challenges or misconceptions that they may face daily. The goal is to provide our students with information/support in hopes that they will become more informed and encouraged about the choices they make. This series is being led and implemented by Ms. Cherry, our new College & Career Coach.

Philander Smith College's 5th Annual African American High School Honor Student Ceremony: Sean Williams, one of our 2020 graduating seniors, was selected and recognized as one of Philander's 5th Annual African American High School Honor Students. In order to qualify students had to have at least a 3.0 GPA as well as be a graduating senior. Sean received a medal, certificate, and even scholarship offers!

post_text: Premier High School - Austin South scholars are ready to rock at Guitar Club! 🎸
shared_text:
Premier High School - Austin South
November 20, 2019 at 5:51 PM ·

Premier High School Guitar Club Update:

We recently received a grant that has everyone excited and ready to make some MUSIC!

This grant has been a donation to the PHS Guitar Club, which will now be exposing students to a variety of instruments including guitar, bass guitar, piano, and drums.

The PHS Guitar Club would like to thank, Guitar Center, Lynn Robison (the Guitar Center rep who approved our grant), and Mike Berryman for all of his help along the way.

Guitar Club is a positive outlet for students to be creative and express themselves. Students interested in joining the group can get in touch with Mr. Padgett.

Here are some of the students opening up their new gear.

post_text: 👏👏 Congratulations, Roman!
shared_text:
Premier High School - San Antonio East is feeling proud.
October 7, 2019 at 10:00 PM ·

Mission of Bexar County Sheriff's Explorers Program
To educate and involve youth in Bexar County operations, to interest them in possible Law Enforcement careers (Sheriff's Deputy, Detention Officer, Sheriff's Dispatcher, Prosecuting Attorney, Crime Lab Technician, etc.) and to build mutual understanding.

Law Enforcement Career Exploring provides educational training programs for young adults on the purposes, mission, and objectives of law enforcement. The program provides career orientation experiences, leadership opportunities, and community service activities.

The primary goals of the program are to help young adults choose a career path within law enforcement and to challenge them to become responsible citizens of their communities and the nation.

Congrats to our own EXPLORER 9th grader Roman Lomeli. Keep making PHS Panthers proud! 😎
